## ğŸš€ Get Running in 5 Steps

### Step 1: Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+ installed: https://nodejs.org/
- Discord account
- Text editor (VS Code recommended)

### Step 2: Get Your Discord Bot Token
1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
2. Click "New Application" â†’ name it "Social Watcher"
3. Click "Bot" â†’ "Add Bot"
4. Under your bot username, click "Reset Token" â†’ "Copy"
5. **KEEP THIS SECRET!**

### Step 3: Setup Project
```powershell
# Navigate to the project folder
cd e:\0nngdiscordbot

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env file from template
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env and paste your bot token
# DISCORD_TOKEN=paste_your_token_here
```

### Step 4: Setup Database
```powershell
npm run prisma:push
```

### Step 5: Run the Bot
```powershell
npm run dev
```

You should see:
```
âœ… Logged in as Social Media Watcher#1234
âœ… Registered 5 slash commands
âœ… Bot is fully operational!
```

## ğŸ® Test It Works

1. Invite your bot to a Discord server: 
   - Replace `YOUR_CLIENT_ID` with your Client ID (from Developer Portal)
   - Visit: `https://discord.com/api/oauth2/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&permissions=274878024704&scope=bot%20applications.commands`

2. In Discord, type:
   ```
   /start
   ```
   â†’ Bot responds with welcome message âœ“

3. Add a social media link:
   ```
   /link add
   ```
   - Platform: YouTube
   - URL: `https://www.youtube.com/@YouTube`
   - Content types: Posts only
   - Channel: #announcements

4. Wait 1 minute â†’ Bot checks for new videos

Done! Your bot is working! ğŸ‰

